Unique to cursor-composer2: none beyond the shared "missing test" call-out.
Unique to gemini-3.1-flash-lite-preview: none тАФ accepted with 0 issues; missed both the Stop() race and the test gap.
Disagreements: verdict тАФ codex rejected (high-severity race), cursor and gemini accepted.

Notes:
- Codex was the only backend to verify lifecycle interactions across `Stop()` and the new read goroutines. Its summary explicitly cites "Bazel unit tests pass" тАФ it actually ran tests as part of the review.
- Gemini-flash-lite continues the pattern from 2026-04-21: very fast (2nd fastest at 130s) but shallow тАФ accepted a diff with a real concurrency bug.
